Before refactoring:
javascript
function calcTotal(a, b) {
  let temp_data_final3 = a + b;
  console.log(temp_data_final3);
  return temp_data_final3;
}

After refactoring:
javascript
function calculateTotal(price, quantity) {
  const total = price * quantity;
  return total;
}

The refactoring improves readability by renaming the function and variables, removing unnecessary logging, and making the logic clearer.
